mponents/sonoff/light.py file with the code solution in this thread, saved, Initialised the Sonoff integration, restarted HA. This did not solve the problem for me. \nAll lights work in the eWeLink app. (I had not used the app in a while and had to re-pair lights.)  \n\nHA Error: \"This entity is no longer being provided by the sonoff integration. If the entity is no longer in use, delete it in settings.\"\nSee diagnostics file below:\n```json\n{\n  \"home_assistant\": {\n    \"installation_type\": \"Home Assistant OS\",\n    \"version\": \"2026.3.0\",\n    \"dev\": false,\n    \"hassio\": true,\n    \"virtualenv\": false,\n    \"python_version\": \"3.14.2\",\n    \"docker\": true,\n    \"arch\": \"aarch64\",\n    \"timezone\": \"Africa/Johannesburg\",\n    \"os_name\": \"Linux\",\n    \"os_version\": \"6.12.47-haos-raspi\",\n    \"container_arch\": \"aarch64\",\n    \"supervisor\": \"2026.02.3\",\n    \"host_os\": \"Home Assistant OS 17.1\",\n    \"docker_version\": \"29.1.3\",\n    \"chassis\": \"embedded\",\n    \"run_as_root\": true\n  },\n  \"custom_components\": {\n    \"mikrotik_router\": {\n      \"documentation\": \"https://github.com/tomaae/homeassistant-mikrotik_router\",\n      \"version\": \"0.0.0\",\n      \"requirements\": [\n        \"librouteros>=3.4.1\",\n        \"mac-vendor-lookup>=0.1.12\"\n      ]\n    },\n    \"llmvision\": {\n      \"documentation\": \"https://llmvision.gitbook.io/getting-started/\",\n      \"version\": \"1.6.0\",\n      \"requirements\": [\n        \"boto3==1.37.1\",\n        \"aiosqlite==0.21.0\",\n        \"aiofile==3.9.0\"\n      ]\n    },\n    \"prometheus_sensor\": {\n      \"documentation\": \"https://github.com/mweinelt/ha-prometheus-sensor\",\n      \"version\": \"1.2.1\",\n      \"requirements\": []\n    },\n    \"alexa_media\": {\n      \"documentation\": \"https://github.com/alandtse/alexa_media_player/wiki\",\n      \"version\": \"5.14.0\",\n      \"requirements\": [\n        \"alexapy==1.29.17\",\n        \"pack