tall everything and start from scratch. I have 9 Sonoff devices. I am afraid of loosing settings, but will reinstall if it fixes my problem. \n\nImportant note. You need to collect debug logs. Perhaps switching to Kelvin somehow broke your lamp model.\nhttps://github.com/AlexxIT/SonoffLAN?tab=readme-ov-file#issues\n@AlexxIT , thank you for the feedback. I finally had time to do some more testing.\nI updated to sonoff integration version: 3.10.1. but still could not get access to the Light bulbs in HA. \nLooking at the known issues in the debug log, it shows that the Lights are skipped because they are encrypted. \nDo you know how to disable the encryption? (I've been using these bulbs with HA for over a year, not sure how encryption got enable.)\nLAN control is enabled on the device in eWeLink\n\nKnown issues Debug log:\n```\n2026-03-08 14:23:12 [D] SysInfo: {'installation_type': 'Home Assistant OS', 'version': '2026.3.0', 'dev': False, 'hassio': True, 'virtualenv': False, 'python_version': '3.14.2', 'docker': True, 'arch': 'aarch64', 'timezone': 'Africa/Johannesburg', 'os_name': 'Linux', 'os_version': '6.12.47-haos-raspi', 'user': 'root', 'container_arch': 'aarch64', 'supervisor': '2026.02.3', 'host_os': 'Home Assistant OS 17.1', 'docker_version': '29.1.3', 'chassis': 'embedded', 'sonoff_version': '3.10.1 (af955f5)'}\n2026-03-08 14:23:12 [D] 5 devices loaded from Cache\n2026-03-08 14:23:12 [D] 1001f53ced UIID 0001 | {'version': 8, 'only_device': {'ota': 'success'}, 'sledOnline': 'on', 'switch': 'on', 'fwVersion': '3.7.6', 'rssi': -77, 'startup': 'stay', 'init': 1, 'pulse': 'off', 'pulseWidth': 500, 'rstReason': 0, 'exccause': 0, 'epc1': 0, 'epc2': 0, 'epc3': 0, 'excvaddr': 0, 'depc': 0, 'longOffline': 1}\n2026-03-08 14:23:12 [D] 1001f587e2 UIID 0001 | {'version': 8, 'only_device': {'ota': 'success'}, 'sledOnline': 'on', 'switch': 'off', 'fwVersion': '3.7.6', 'rssi': -61, 'startup': 'off', 'init': 1, 'pulse': 'off', 'pulseWidth': 500, 'rstReason': 0, 'exccause': 0, 