t's more reliable to add devices to ewelink. But then you need to use your account login and password for integration.\nThank you for the feedback. I did not know that the device should not be added in eWeLink for DIY mode. How do you pair the device to HA in DIY mode then?\nI have not tried setting up an account with password. I will try that next.\nIt worked! Thank you for nudging me in the right direction @AlexxIT.\nI did a password reset on eWeLink, Re-added the integration with a password and it worked.\nI am not sure if a had a password from when I set it up originally. The integration did not error when I left the password out, so never tried capturing the password when I started having issues. \n\n", "commit_urls": ["https://github.com/AlexxIT/SonoffLAN/commit/d66bb9fc2815411cec3da157206d15e878cf3912", "https://github.com/AlexxIT/SonoffLAN/commit/9c2ea722558fdc0b85ef295c40a79fa0abaffe90", "https://github.com/AlexxIT/SonoffLAN/commit/ec15a0a65736bb60d241e8b84023babc46cd491c", "https://github.com/AlexxIT/SonoffLAN/commit/ce453816dce7533dc5dace1788eb0e52ef435941", "https://github.com/AlexxIT/SonoffLAN/commit/9661b41c5b0ffb6ec0c97bf44fd422489cef7644"], "created_at": "2026-03-05T02:16:12Z"}
